         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Memo. for the Director of the Botanic Gardens. ¶  ¶ The Chief Secretary's attention has been called to a letter in "The Argus" of yesterday's date signed W. Fergusson and written apparently from the B...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.05.21a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 1226, unit 20, p. 2, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Memo. for the Director of the Botanic Gardens.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Chief Secretary's attention has been called to a letter in "The Argus" of yesterday's date signed W. Fergusson and written apparently from the Botanic Gardens.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>'Destruction of trees in the Botanical Reserve', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 20 May 1870, p. 5. See also M to W. Odgers, 20 May 1870 (in this edition as 70-05-20c), and W. Odgers to M, 21 May 1870.</p>
               </note> Sir Jas. McCulloch desires to know if Mr. Fergusson who holds the office of Inspector of State Forests &amp;c is the author of the letter in question and if so what explanation he has to offer for this violation of the 21st Civil Service Regulation.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For reply, see M to J. McCulloch, 25 May 1870.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">21st May 1870.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
